collectible.name: The Book of Sight
collectible.author: 0x5aaef3cc9c1fb5cb3e771f77979d08b3440f2674
collectible.description: There are several sigils scrawled into this tome, nearby photos of plants and mushrooms. It's hard to make out what it all means. Described are some celestial guardians with answers to pressing questions. Also there are methods of cleanliness and focus.. clean air and self love.. hmm.. a piece of parchment with a quote from another book is left inside: ‚ÄúIt's a very salutary thing to realize that the rather dull universe in which most of us spend most of our time is not the only universe there is. I think it's healthy that people should have this experience.‚Äù ‚Äï Aldous Huxley, Moksha: Writings on Psychedelics & the Visionary Experience. Hmm seems like a wonderful thing, but one should use this book sparingly and if fishing for Sight, bring back not the fish that is too big.. nor the fish that is too small. Bring back the middle sized fish, and practically apply the insight. I think I'm starting to get it.

collectible.name: The Book of Time
collectible.author: 0x5aaef3cc9c1fb5cb3e771f77979d08b3440f2674
collectible.description: Unfortunately not a time traveling book. This tome is about how to prioritize what is important to you in the different spheres of your life. What would you like your life to look like in 5 minutes, in 1 day, in 1 week, 1 month, 3 months, 6 months, 1 year, 3 years, 5 years, 20 years... and to know that these wishes can sometimes change. There are different categories listed like work, recreation, family, relationships, health, skills, aesthetics, athletics, and more. What is in our power to control at a given time? How might one invest in oneself first? What concrete details does wealth look like to you.. or happiness... or community? There are some blank pages for writing, but these pages look weathered. When was the last time you sat and checked in on yourself? The leaves are falling and times are changing. Let's re-examine everything and dust out the old ways.

collectible.name: The Book of Love
collectible.author: 0x5aaef3cc9c1fb5cb3e771f77979d08b3440f2674
collectible.description: A book containing love spells, crush diary entries, and partial lyrics to an ancient song of the heart: "The book of love is long and boring. No one can lift the damn thing. It's full of charts and facts, and figures. And instructions for dancing. But I... I love it when you read to me. And you... You can read me anything. The book of love has music in it. In fact that's where music comes from. Some of it's just transcendental. Some of it's just really dumb. But I... I love it when you sing to me. And you... You can sing me anything." A note is scrawled inside of the back cover, "No matter the circumstances, when you feel a lack of love or you feel heartbreak, like the world is crumbling down inside your chest, know that love is still there if you are patient and wait... wait....."

collectible.name: The Book of Great Falls: Night Edition
collectible.author: 0x5aaef3cc9c1fb5cb3e771f77979d08b3440f2674
collectible.description: This tome contains the remaining (20%) akashic records of Rye's late father. The Great Falls were his main meditation area and so a place where many ashes were scattered. The Falls formed the last time sea level dropped, during the Last Glacial Period about 35,000 years ago. Now a fallen king became a part of the Falls forever. This book wields all the secrets and mistakes that were in and around Rye's father's life. This hidden knowledge is important for the journey of strength and humility, but what page does your bookmark land on?

collectible.name: The Book of Great Falls: Day Edition
collectible.author: 0x5aaef3cc9c1fb5cb3e771f77979d08b3440f2674
collectible.description: This tome contains the near-full (80%) akashic records of Rye's late father. The Great Falls were his main meditation area and so a place where many ashes were scattered. The rocks of the falls date to the late Precambrian times and are about 750 million years old. The rocks are a resistant metamorphized schist, gneisses, metagraywackes, and metaconglomerates. Now a fallen king became a part of the Falls forever. This book wields all the good that Rye's father has done for himself and for others. This knowledge is important for the journey of joy and inspiration, but what page does your bookmark land on?
